    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-01T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-01T22:00:00-05:00" n="863"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/917: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dooman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-02T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 2, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 2—4
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>451. Department’s 183, August 30, 6 p.m., to Peiping. I delivered yesterday at
                    the Foreign Office a first person note<note n="11" xml:id="d863fn11">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_748">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 748</ref>. For the Japanese reply, No.
                        204, December 28, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_750">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 750</ref>. For second Japanese note,
                        No. 12, January 25, 1940, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_753">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 753</ref>.</note> protesting against
                    seizure and occupation of Swatow Customs. Having done so, I invited the British
                    and French Ambassadors to take similar action. They are consulting their
                    respective Governments.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping. Peiping please repeat to Chungking and Swatow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dooman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
